02:07.036 --> 02:09.913
<i>She was Lo. Plain Lo in the morning.</i>

02:10.872 --> 02:13.042
<i>Standing four feet ten in one sock.</i>

02:14.210 --> 02:16.212
<i>She was Lola in slacks.</i>

02:16.421 --> 02:18.423
<i>She was Dolly at school.</i>

02:19.215 --> 02:21.384
<i>She was Dolores on the dotted line.</i>

02:22.635 --> 02:25.054
<i>In my arms, she was always...</i>

02:25.221 --> 02:27.223
<i>..Lolita.</i>

02:28.933 --> 02:30.935
<i>Light of my life.</i>

02:31.102 --> 02:33.104
<i>Fire of my loins.</i>

02:33.271 --> 02:34.856
<i>My sin.</i>

02:35.022 --> 02:36.607
<i>My soul.</i>

02:36.774 --> 02:38.776
<i>Lolita.</i>

02:42.864 --> 02:45.867
<i>But there might have been
no Lolita at all...</i>

02:46.034 --> 02:48.036
<i>..had I not first met Annabel.</i>

02:55.835 --> 02:57.837
<i>We were both 14.</i>

02:58.838 --> 03:02.300
<i>Whatever happens to a boy
during the summer he's 14...</i>

03:02.467 --> 03:04.594
<i>..can mark him for life.</i>

03:15.813 --> 03:18.066
<i>That hotel you see, the Mirana,...</i>

03:18.232 --> 03:19.817
<i>..that belonged to us.</i>

03:41.923 --> 03:43.925
<i>She wanted to be a nurse.</i>

03:47.470 --> 03:49.472
<i>I wanted to be a spy.</i>

03:53.976 --> 03:58.231
<i>All at once we were madly,
hopelessly in love.</i>

04:41.149 --> 04:43.568
<i>Four months later, she died of typhus.</i>

04:53.578 --> 04:56.372
<i>The shock of her death
froze something in me.</i>

04:56.539 --> 04:58.541
<i>The child I loved was gone.</i>

05:00.752 --> 05:02.754
<i>But I kept looking for her...</i>

05:03.671 --> 05:06.716
<i>..long after I'd left
my own childhood behind.</i>

05:12.847 --> 05:15.099
<i>The poison was in the wound, you see.</i>

05:15.266 --> 05:17.268
<i>And the wound wouldn't heal.</i>

05:28.237 --> 05:31.199
<i>I probably should have
joined the priesthood.</i>

05:31.366 --> 05:35.787
<i>Instead, I accepted a teaching post
at Beardsley College in America.</i>

05:37.372 --> 05:40.041
<i>I had a summer free
before the Fall semester.</i>

05:40.208 --> 05:43.086
<i>I thought I'd finish
a textbook I was working on.</i>

05:43.252 --> 05:46.464
<i>A survey of French literature
for American students.</i>

05:52.762 --> 05:54.764
<i>I took my advance...</i>

05:54.931 --> 05:59.852
<i>..and went to live at the house of friends
of my late uncle's, the McCoos,...</i>

06:00.019 --> 06:02.438
<i>..in the New England town of Ramsdale.</i>

06:05.066 --> 06:08.319
<i>But on arriving, I found
that it was no longer there.</i>

06:13.032 --> 06:14.826
<i>However, a friend of Mrs McCoo,...</i>

06:14.992 --> 06:17.078
<i>..a widow, Mrs Charlotte Haze,...</i>

06:17.245 --> 06:19.038
<i>..agreed to accommodate me.</i>

06:28.548 --> 06:31.259
- Goddamn dog!

06:56.993 --> 06:59.203
One minute. Something's burnin'.

06:59.370 --> 07:00.830
Lord have mercy!

07:00.997 --> 07:02.999
Mrs Haze'll be down in one.

07:05.043 --> 07:09.589
Is that Professor Humbert,
Louise? Tell him I'll be down in one.

07:09.756 --> 07:12.592
She'll be down in one!

07:19.891 --> 07:21.267
Monsieur Humbert.

07:22.685 --> 07:24.353
Uh, yes.

07:24.520 --> 07:26.522
Mrs Haze, is it?

07:27.690 --> 07:29.692
Charlotte.

07:29.859 --> 07:32.445
I am so pleased
to make your acquaintance.

07:32.612 --> 07:36.032
Frank McCoo told me all about
your scholarly pursuits.

07:38.284 --> 07:41.245
I myself just cherish the French tongue.

07:42.580 --> 07:44.582
Um... I wonder, could I...

07:44.749 --> 07:46.584
Mm. Come in.

07:48.544 --> 07:50.755
Harold and I, the late Mr Haze,...

07:50.922 --> 07:52.882
..we simply adored Mexico.

07:53.049 --> 07:56.302
The whole idea
of a culture that sophisticated.

07:56.469 --> 07:58.721
And we think of them as primitive.

07:58.888 --> 08:00.890
I mean, look at us!

08:01.891 --> 08:03.434
Indeed, yes.

08:04.102 --> 08:06.104
Upstairs.

08:06.270 --> 08:08.356
I and Lo have our rooms just there.

08:09.774 --> 08:11.776
And this is your room.

08:11.943 --> 08:14.195
Space for a desk, anything you want.

08:15.863 --> 08:18.866
And at $20 a month,
you can't beat the price.

08:20.326 --> 08:23.121
And here's the bathroom.
It's a bit of a mess.

08:32.462 --> 08:34.881
And this is the kitchen.

08:35.049 --> 08:39.010
Now, if you have any special
food needs, you just say.

08:39.178 --> 08:43.765
I don't know if Ramsdale can provide you
with foie grass, like you're used to.

08:43.933 --> 08:45.435
What's that?

08:46.561 --> 08:49.021
Uh... timetable. For when I um...

08:49.188 --> 08:53.651
I was hoping I wouldn't have to,
but I think I've got to go back to New York.

08:53.818 --> 08:58.823
- Oh, you're not too favourably impressed.
- No... There's a Baudelaire conference...

08:58.990 --> 09:03.327
This is not a neat household,
but you would be very comfortable here.

09:03.494 --> 09:05.329
Very comfortable indeed.

09:05.496 --> 09:08.541
Don't say no until you've seen the piazza.

09:08.708 --> 09:10.710
Come.

09:12.086 --> 09:14.088
Well, I call it the piazza.

09:16.007 --> 09:19.510
It's so much work
to keep it healthy and green.

09:20.720 --> 09:22.722
It's a life's work.

09:24.348 --> 09:26.350
That's my Lo.

09:33.900 --> 09:35.902
And these are my lilies.

09:37.570 --> 09:39.572
I love lilies.

09:39.739 --> 09:43.534
- Lily's a nice name, don't you think?
- Beautiful.

10:30.081 --> 10:32.083
Beautiful!

10:32.792 --> 10:34.711
How much did you say the room was?

11:31.184 --> 11:33.186
<i>A normal man,...</i>

11:33.352 --> 11:36.314
<i>..given a group photograph
of schoolgirls...</i>

11:36.481 --> 11:40.276
<i>..and asked to point out
the loveliest one,...</i>

11:40.443 --> 11:44.030
<i>..will not necessarily choose
the nymphet among them.</i>

11:46.824 --> 11:48.826
<i>You have to be an artist,...</i>

11:50.119 --> 11:55.375
<i>..a madman, full of shame
and melancholy and despair,...</i>

11:55.541 --> 11:59.754
<i>..in order to recognise the little
deadly demon among the others.</i>

12:02.215 --> 12:04.217
<i>She stands...</i>

12:05.718 --> 12:08.763
<i>..unrecognised by them,...</i>

12:08.930 --> 12:12.600
<i>..unconscious herself
of her fantastic power.</i>

12:16.687 --> 12:20.191
- See you later, alligator.
- After a while, crocodile!

12:20.358 --> 12:23.611
- Real soon, Daniel Boone.
- Get fucked, Daffy Duck.

12:46.217 --> 12:52.181
<i># Don't know why...
there's no sun up in the sky</i>

12:52.348 --> 12:55.435
<i># Stormy weather</i>

12:55.893 --> 13:00.273
<i># Since my man and I ain't together...</i>

13:00.440 --> 13:02.442
You woke me up.

13:03.443 --> 13:06.029
- Sorry.

13:09.323 --> 13:11.492
I'll stop.

14:52.552 --> 14:55.430
Dolores!
Have you made your bed?

14:56.431 --> 14:58.224
No, I have not made my bed.

14:58.391 --> 15:01.185
I asked you to make your bed, didn't I?

15:01.352 --> 15:04.063
No. You asked me if I'd made my bed.

15:04.939 --> 15:06.941
Make your bed.

15:08.317 --> 15:10.111
- Now!

15:10.278 --> 15:12.363
<i>I long for some terrific disaster.</i>

15:12.530 --> 15:14.490
<i>Earthquake.</i>

15:14.657 --> 15:16.659
<i>Spectacular explosion.</i>

15:16.826 --> 15:18.619
Make your bed!

15:18.786 --> 15:21.748
<i>Her mother instantly eliminated.</i>

15:23.291 --> 15:26.085
<i>Along with everybody else
for miles around.</i>

15:29.213 --> 15:31.215
<i>Lolita...</i>

15:31.382 --> 15:33.384
<i>..in my arms.</i>

16:07.001 --> 16:09.003
I'm sleepy today.

16:09.962 --> 16:12.048
Me too.

16:13.591 --> 16:16.052
Have you been having trouble sleeping?

16:17.637 --> 16:19.889
You can't imagine.

16:54.966 --> 16:56.551
Am I getting a zit?

16:58.136 --> 17:00.138
What?

17:00.304 --> 17:02.306
Do you see a pimple on my chin?

17:08.604 --> 17:11.315
You look absolutely perfect to me.

17:12.775 --> 17:14.944
Wanna see my chin wobble?

17:16.237 --> 17:17.905
OK.

17:26.998 --> 17:29.000
Humbert!

17:39.594 --> 17:40.636
Humbert...

17:42.346 --> 17:44.557
Is she keeping you up?

17:46.309 --> 17:48.311
I beg your pardon?

17:48.686 --> 17:50.229
No!

17:50.396 --> 17:51.731
No. No, I'm...

17:52.982 --> 17:54.984
No.

17:57.528 --> 18:00.281
Well, it's probably just a 24-hour bug.

18:00.448 --> 18:02.867
He was looking forward to meeting you.

18:03.034 --> 18:05.286
Has anybody seen my other sneaker?!

18:19.217 --> 18:21.552
Your breakfast, Professor Humbert.

18:28.351 --> 18:31.229
Don't tell Mother, but I ate all your bacon.

18:39.696 --> 18:42.824
- Dolores, that was Mrs Farlow.
- So?

18:42.990 --> 18:46.202
Rose has a temperature
and can't go to Hourglass Lake.

18:46.369 --> 18:48.663
- Oh, yeah?
- Do not use that tone with me!

18:48.830 --> 18:50.707
Are you ready for church?

18:50.873 --> 18:53.459
I'm not going to that disgusting church.

18:53.626 --> 18:56.671
- Young lady...
- No picnic, no church.

18:56.838 --> 18:59.674
That is fine with me.
It is your conscience.

18:59.841 --> 19:02.844
I want your room spick-and-span
when I get home.

19:03.010 --> 19:05.972
- And wash your hair, young lady.
- I did wash it!

19:06.139 --> 19:08.141
- When?
- A couple of months ago.

19:28.995 --> 19:30.997
I could be a dancer.

19:34.292 --> 19:36.294
That's a major option.

19:41.007 --> 19:43.009
Cos I do have a natural grace.

19:44.677 --> 19:48.514
- You know. A kind of sad beauty.
- Sort of sad is right.

19:51.392 --> 19:53.561
I'd like to see you dance sometime.

19:53.728 --> 19:57.231
Little girls always want to be
ballerinas, don't they?

19:57.398 --> 19:59.400
I know I did.

19:59.567 --> 20:02.779
But I was - how should I put it? -
a tad too... plump?

20:02.945 --> 20:05.031
- Is that the right word?
- Yes.

20:08.368 --> 20:10.370
I'll get more Vouvray.

20:15.917 --> 20:19.003
Make her take us
to Hourglass Lake tomorrow.

20:19.170 --> 20:21.464
- Me?
- Mm-hm.

20:21.631 --> 20:23.633
She'll do anything you say.

20:23.800 --> 20:25.968
She's getting a thing about you.

20:36.521 --> 20:38.523
Whisper, whisper.

20:38.689 --> 20:41.067
What are you two so cosy about?

20:41.234 --> 20:43.903
Um... Did I ever tell you both that...

20:45.154 --> 20:47.115
..I was once a...

20:47.281 --> 20:49.283
..that I was once a... um...

20:51.369 --> 20:54.914
Uh... that I...
I was once a cook in the North Pole?

20:55.081 --> 20:57.750
- A cook?
- Well, not exactly a cook.

20:57.875 --> 20:59.877
I opened a few cans.

21:01.796 --> 21:05.216
It was a weather expedition.
And I shot a polar bear.

21:05.383 --> 21:07.385
- No!
- Well, I didn't hit it.

21:07.552 --> 21:10.638
Why shoot a polar bear?
That's a lousy thing to do.

21:10.805 --> 21:13.391
Because I found it...

21:13.558 --> 21:17.103
..with its face - listen to this -
in the ice-cream mixer.

21:18.980 --> 21:22.316
I couldn't let that pass
because we lived off ice cream.

21:25.987 --> 21:27.989
You're out of your gourd, Humpy.

21:29.615 --> 21:32.035
Will you stop fidgeting with the doll?

21:33.661 --> 21:36.372
And now we all think
that Lo should go to bed.

21:36.539 --> 21:38.541
Lo?

21:38.708 --> 21:40.710
What do you mean "we", paleface?

21:42.003 --> 21:46.174
So, as I was saying, there I was
with my white polar-bear gun...

21:48.217 --> 21:50.887
- ..to blend in.

21:51.054 --> 21:53.056
It's for me!

21:55.391 --> 21:56.350
Hello?

21:57.185 --> 22:02.190
- No, I'm sorry. She's busy.
- I hope you will forgive her bad manners.

22:02.356 --> 22:04.317
- Now what?!

22:04.484 --> 22:07.028
Look! It's my modern dance creation!

22:11.741 --> 22:14.869
Dolores Haze, turn that music down!

22:17.497 --> 22:21.876
She is a pest. Just slap her hard
if she interferes with your meditations.

22:25.004 --> 22:26.422
Psst!

22:39.102 --> 22:40.853
Hum...

22:41.020 --> 22:45.441
Hum, do you know that I have
one most ambitious dream?

22:45.608 --> 22:47.944
To get a hold of a real trained maid...

22:48.111 --> 22:51.447
..like that German girl
that the Talbots spoke of...

22:51.614 --> 22:53.616
..and have her live in the house.

22:53.783 --> 22:55.785
- No room.
- Oh, chéri, chéri.

22:55.952 --> 22:59.997
You underestimate the possibilities
of our humble household.

23:00.164 --> 23:02.250
We'd put her in Lo's room.

23:02.417 --> 23:05.962
I intended to turn that hole
into a guest room anyway.

23:06.129 --> 23:08.131
But where would Lo sleep?

23:08.297 --> 23:11.592
Little Lo does not enter the picture at all.

23:11.759 --> 23:15.722
Little Lo goes straight from camp
to a good boarding school...

23:15.888 --> 23:19.851
..with strict discipline
and some sound religious training.

23:22.979 --> 23:24.939
I won't go!

23:25.106 --> 23:29.402
I want all of these name tags
sewn on your clothes by tomorrow.

23:30.945 --> 23:32.947
I don't want to go.

23:33.114 --> 23:34.741
I didn't ask your opinion!

23:34.907 --> 23:37.326
I don't want to go and you can't make me.

23:37.493 --> 23:40.663
Look, we all think it's a good idea.

23:40.830 --> 23:45.626
Professor Humbert thinks it's a good idea,
I think it's a good idea, and you are going!

23:49.088 --> 23:50.673
Double-crosser!

23:51.340 --> 23:53.051
Ow!

23:54.010 --> 23:58.097
I asked you to put that suitcase
in the car an hour ago!

23:58.306 --> 24:01.642
Louise, thank you so much
for helping the poor child.

24:04.062 --> 24:08.983
Goddamn it! Dolores, I told you
to put this lunch basket in the back seat!

24:09.150 --> 24:11.361
Why always tell me to do everything?

24:11.527 --> 24:13.738
I'm the one that won't be eating it.

24:13.905 --> 24:17.158
Louise! Brussels sprouts
and meat loaf for dinner.

24:17.325 --> 24:20.411
- All right. Drive careful.
- Thank you. Let's go!

24:20.578 --> 24:22.580
- Bye, my baby.
- Bye, Louise.

24:22.747 --> 24:25.249
- You be good. I'm gonna miss you.
- Agh!

24:26.709 --> 24:28.711
Dolores!

24:28.878 --> 24:31.005
Let's go!

24:31.172 --> 24:32.965
Speed it up!

24:33.132 --> 24:34.884
Get in the car!

24:39.847 --> 24:42.600
Now what?! That child!

24:47.730 --> 24:50.400
- Louise, maybe tenderloin.
- That'd be good.

25:38.489 --> 25:40.491
I'm waiting!

25:41.325 --> 25:44.704
If I've told you once,
I've told you a thousand times...

25:44.871 --> 25:47.290
..not to make me wait in the car.

25:48.499 --> 25:51.753
If you weren't going to camp,
I would ground you.

26:15.818 --> 26:17.820
Mr Humble!

26:17.987 --> 26:20.865
These damn stairs
are gonna be the death of me.

26:21.032 --> 26:22.784
Mr Humble!

26:24.077 --> 26:25.661
Mr Humble!

26:25.828 --> 26:27.830
Mr Humble?

26:31.876 --> 26:33.878
I have something for you.

26:34.045 --> 26:36.214
Oh, yes.

26:36.381 --> 26:39.717
I'm leaving, but I'll be back later.

26:43.012 --> 26:45.598
What the hell he doin' in there?

26:49.310 --> 26:51.521
"This is a confession.

26:51.687 --> 26:53.690
I love you.

26:53.856 --> 26:56.192
I'm a passionate and lonely woman...

26:56.359 --> 26:58.361
..and you are the love of my life.

26:58.528 --> 27:00.530
Now you know.

27:00.697 --> 27:03.116
So please, destroy this letter and go.

27:04.033 --> 27:07.620
I shall return by dinner time
and you must be gone by then.

27:09.330 --> 27:11.874
You see, chéri, if I found you at home,...

27:12.041 --> 27:15.545
..the fact of your remaining
would mean only one thing.

27:15.712 --> 27:19.882
That you want me as much as I do you,
as a lifelong mate,...

27:20.049 --> 27:24.971
..and that you are ready to link up
your life with mine for ever and ever...

27:25.138 --> 27:27.974
..and be a father to my little girl."

27:30.184 --> 27:34.856
<i>Two weeks later,
we were married in a simple ceremony.</i>

27:35.023 --> 27:39.193
<i>Big Haze made sure little Haze
was not in attendance.</i>

27:44.741 --> 27:46.743
Mm. This is bliss.

27:46.909 --> 27:49.328
This is heaven on earth.
Isn't it, Hump?

27:49.495 --> 27:51.497
Mm.

27:54.792 --> 27:57.295
Are you working on your book?

27:57.462 --> 27:59.464
Yes.

28:07.472 --> 28:09.807
Oh, a secret drawer.
What's in there?

28:11.642 --> 28:13.644
Locked-up love letters.

28:15.146 --> 28:17.148
Where's the key?

28:18.107 --> 28:20.401
Hidden.

28:27.158 --> 28:30.286
<i>During the six weeks
we'd been married,...</i>

28:30.453 --> 28:33.956
<i>..I successfully avoided
most of my husbandly duties.</i>

28:37.418 --> 28:42.048
<i>Throughout July, I'd been offering
Charlotte various sleeping tablets,...</i>

28:42.215 --> 28:44.384
<i>..which she gobbled down happily.</i>

28:44.550 --> 28:46.552
<i>She was a great taker of pills.</i>

28:49.055 --> 28:52.934
<i># I'm in the mood for love</i>

28:53.851 --> 28:57.480
<i># Simply because you're near me</i>

28:58.272 --> 29:01.901
<i># Funny, but when you're near me</i>

29:02.568 --> 29:06.197
<i># I'm in the mood for love</i>

29:07.365 --> 29:10.952
<i># Heaven is in your eyes</i>

29:11.119 --> 29:14.706
<i># Bright as the stars we're under</i>

29:15.832 --> 29:19.335
<i># Oh, is it any wonder...</i>

29:19.502 --> 29:23.214
<i>The last dose I had tried
had knocked her out for four hours.</i>

29:23.381 --> 29:27.427
<i>But that was not enough
to guarantee me an undisturbed night.</i>

29:30.388 --> 29:32.390
Hum...

29:33.224 --> 29:35.226
At last!

29:37.311 --> 29:38.688
Mm.

29:40.815 --> 29:42.817
I think I must be immune.

29:45.945 --> 29:49.032
Wh... What would you give me
if you wanted to uh...

29:49.198 --> 29:50.950
..to knock out...

29:51.117 --> 29:52.827
..say, a cow?

29:54.454 --> 29:57.582
J-Just for... seven or eight hours.

29:57.749 --> 29:59.333
So that...

30:01.169 --> 30:04.505
..you know, the cow... would stay asleep?

30:07.008 --> 30:10.511
Even if you were
tossing and turning next to it.

30:11.554 --> 30:13.181
Well...

30:13.347 --> 30:14.724
Why don't you...

30:14.891 --> 30:16.476
..try these?

30:16.642 --> 30:18.227
They're new.

30:19.771 --> 30:22.231
My wife takes them and...

30:22.398 --> 30:25.902
..I don't hear a peep out of her
all night long.

30:27.236 --> 30:29.238
Sounds like just the thing.

30:41.334 --> 30:43.336
I'm home!

30:46.047 --> 30:47.632
Hello?

30:52.845 --> 30:54.430
Hello?

30:55.765 --> 30:57.350
Hello?

31:07.568 --> 31:09.570
"The Haze woman."

31:11.155 --> 31:13.157
"The fat cow"?

31:15.576 --> 31:17.578
"The obnoxious mamma"?

31:21.165 --> 31:25.878
Well, the "old stupid Haze woman"
is no longer your dupe.

31:26.045 --> 31:28.423
Charlotte!

31:30.633 --> 31:33.094
You're a monster.

31:33.261 --> 31:36.723
- You're a despicable, criminal monster.

31:36.889 --> 31:39.559
- Now...
- If you come near me I'll scream!

31:39.726 --> 31:41.811
- Let me just...
- Get away from me!

31:41.978 --> 31:44.105
I'm leaving tonight.

31:44.272 --> 31:46.607
You can keep this house.
I don't care.

31:48.067 --> 31:53.197
But you will never see
that miserable brat ever again.

31:55.950 --> 31:58.703
Now get out of my sight!

32:16.554 --> 32:18.556
Charlotte, you mustn't...

32:18.723 --> 32:20.725
You mustn't ruin our lives.

32:23.144 --> 32:25.146
That's...

32:25.313 --> 32:29.734
That's just...
That's just a fragment of...

32:29.901 --> 32:32.028
..a novel I'm writing.

32:33.946 --> 32:36.282
I used your name on those...

32:36.449 --> 32:38.701
..just for... convenience.

32:41.120 --> 32:43.122
I'll get us a drink.

32:59.347 --> 33:02.558
A nice stiff drink
will clear both our heads.

33:08.064 --> 33:10.483
Charlotte,
I made us a nice stiff drink!

33:12.735 --> 33:14.737
Yes?

33:16.239 --> 33:18.241
But that's ridiculous.

33:19.158 --> 33:23.996
There's this man on the phone
saying you've been killed, Charlotte.

33:24.872 --> 33:26.249
Charlotte?

34:07.248 --> 34:09.583
I'm... I'm sorry.

34:14.964 --> 34:17.050
Stand back, please.

34:18.092 --> 34:20.219
Where's my wife?

34:21.054 --> 34:24.474
- Are you Mr Humbert?
- I am.

34:26.516 --> 34:28.518
She ran right in front of me.

34:28.686 --> 34:30.855
I... I didn't even see her.

34:35.068 --> 34:36.902
Sir?

34:41.282 --> 34:43.284
I'm sorry, sir.

34:43.451 --> 34:45.411
Is this Mrs Humbert?

34:48.831 --> 34:50.375
Sir,...

34:50.541 --> 34:52.585
..is this Mrs Humbert?

34:55.670 --> 34:57.632
Oh, God...

34:58.841 --> 35:02.095
Oh, God... Oh, God!

35:14.440 --> 35:16.818
She was walking to the mailbox.

35:18.027 --> 35:20.279
She was going to mail these letters.

35:22.031 --> 35:23.616
I'm sorry.

35:24.742 --> 35:26.786
Thank you.

35:30.456 --> 35:32.875
I'll go and... lie down, officer.

35:33.084 --> 35:36.170
- Will that be all right?
- You go right ahead, sir.

35:36.337 --> 35:39.298
I'll just be across in the house if you...

37:09.222 --> 37:11.557
Is that the Enchanted Hunters Hotel?

37:11.724 --> 37:13.726
Yes. This is Mr Humbert.

37:13.893 --> 37:15.853
Tomorrow night.

37:16.020 --> 37:18.022
Just the one night, please.

37:19.899 --> 37:21.901
Yes, a room with twin beds.

37:22.068 --> 37:25.613
For two.
Well, one and a half people, really.

37:25.780 --> 37:27.657
It's just for me and my...

37:27.824 --> 37:31.577
..my short... my small daughter.

38:09.782 --> 38:11.701
She should be here any minute.

38:12.201 --> 38:14.954
I sent Charlie for her over at the barn.

38:16.998 --> 38:19.459
- Who's Charlie?
- Come on, come on.

38:21.502 --> 38:25.298
It's such a pleasure to watch
our young people make friends.

38:25.465 --> 38:28.176
- So uh... who is this Charlie?
- Here she is.

38:41.814 --> 38:43.649
Hi, Dad!

38:43.816 --> 38:47.153
# Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum

38:47.320 --> 38:51.324
# Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum

38:51.491 --> 38:53.910
# Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum...

38:54.077 --> 38:57.747
- How's Mum?
- Well... The doctors aren't quite sure.

38:57.914 --> 39:00.166
It's something abdominal.

39:02.502 --> 39:04.003
Abominable?

39:04.670 --> 39:06.172
Abdominal.

39:11.969 --> 39:15.473
She's in a special hospital
over in Lepingville.

39:15.640 --> 39:18.309
So... I thought we'd... we'd...

39:18.476 --> 39:20.853
..go over to Briceland,...

39:21.020 --> 39:24.774
..spend the night there and...
visit the hospital tomorrow.

39:24.941 --> 39:26.776
Or the next day.

39:32.031 --> 39:34.200
So, did you have a good time at camp?

39:34.367 --> 39:36.160
Mm-hm.

39:37.495 --> 39:39.497
You know, I missed you.

39:39.664 --> 39:41.666
I missed you a lot.

39:41.833 --> 39:44.419
Well, I didn't miss you.

39:44.585 --> 39:47.755
In fact, I've been
revoltingly unfaithful to you.

39:47.922 --> 39:51.426
But so what? Cos you don't care
about me any more anyway.

39:51.592 --> 39:54.595
Why do you think I don't care about you?

39:54.762 --> 39:57.807
Well, you haven't
kissed me yet, have you?

40:26.169 --> 40:27.628
Oh!

40:28.838 --> 40:32.383
- Uh, I'm sorry, officer.
- See a blue sedan, same make as yours?

40:32.550 --> 40:37.513
- They might have passed you at the turn.
- Blue sedan? No, I don't think... agh!

40:37.680 --> 40:41.517
- We didn't see a blue sedan.
- No, I don't think we did.

40:41.684 --> 40:45.104
Are you sure it was blue?
I saw one that was more purple.

40:45.271 --> 40:47.398
Or maybe it was more red.

40:47.565 --> 40:49.650
All right, OK. Thank you.

40:50.526 --> 40:53.279
- Thank you!

40:53.446 --> 40:55.782
Don't shoot, don't shoot!

41:11.506 --> 41:13.508
Wow! Looks swank!

41:23.351 --> 41:25.895
<i># No, I will never tell lies</i>

41:26.062 --> 41:29.023
<i># But still I'm called Buttercup...</i>

41:29.190 --> 41:33.069
Good evening. I have a reservation
in the name of Humbert.

41:33.236 --> 41:35.238
Twin-bedded room.

41:35.405 --> 41:38.074
I called last night.

41:38.241 --> 41:40.910
- Two people.
- Oh!

41:41.035 --> 41:42.829
I'm sorry, Mr Humbug.

41:42.995 --> 41:48.334
I held the room with the twin beds for you
till 6:30, but I didn't hear from you.

41:48.459 --> 41:53.965
We hold till 6:30. And with the flower
show and Glory of Christ convention...

41:54.132 --> 41:56.384
My name is not Humbug. It's Herbert.

41:56.968 --> 41:58.469
Humbert.

41:59.846 --> 42:04.100
Just put us in any room. Put a cot in
for my daughter. She's very tired.

42:06.519 --> 42:09.939
Perhaps I could put you in room 342.
It has a double bed.

42:10.106 --> 42:13.568
I expect we'll manage.
My wife may be turning up later.

42:17.447 --> 42:19.449
Please sign here, mister.

42:25.788 --> 42:27.957
It's a nice dog, huh?

42:28.124 --> 42:30.126
I love dogs.

42:32.170 --> 42:34.172
Well, that's my dog.

42:34.338 --> 42:36.049
He likes you.

42:36.215 --> 42:38.760
Doesn't like everybody.

42:41.012 --> 42:43.014
Who does he like?

42:44.182 --> 42:46.351
He can smell when people are sweet.

42:47.393 --> 42:49.270
He likes sweet people.

42:49.437 --> 42:51.939
Nice young people.

42:52.106 --> 42:54.108
Like you.

43:03.034 --> 43:05.036
Here we are.

43:25.264 --> 43:27.266
Thanks very much.

43:29.519 --> 43:32.397
Wait a sec. You mean
we're sleeping in one room?

43:34.273 --> 43:36.401
With one bed?

43:36.567 --> 43:38.903
I've asked them to send up a cot,...

43:39.070 --> 43:41.072
..which I'll use, if you like.

43:45.368 --> 43:47.120
You're crazy.

43:47.286 --> 43:49.831
Why, my darling?

43:49.997 --> 43:51.999
Because, my darling,...

43:52.166 --> 43:56.713
..when my darling mother finds out,
she'll divorce you and strangle me.

43:56.879 --> 43:58.381
Lo,...

43:58.548 --> 44:00.550
..listen to me a moment.

44:00.717 --> 44:03.678
For all practical purposes,
I am your father,...

44:03.845 --> 44:06.264
..and I'm responsible for your welfare.

44:06.431 --> 44:08.975
Now, we're not rich.

44:09.142 --> 44:13.771
So when we travel, we-we're sure to be...
I mean, we'll be thrown together.

44:16.149 --> 44:17.400
Sometimes.

44:17.567 --> 44:20.528
Two people sharing
the same hotel room...

44:20.695 --> 44:23.614
..are bound to... enter into a...

44:23.781 --> 44:25.950
How can I put it? Into a kind of um...

44:26.200 --> 44:28.202
The word is "incest".

44:43.426 --> 44:46.095
I feel like we're grown-ups.

44:46.220 --> 44:48.222
Me too.

44:48.389 --> 44:50.767
We get to do whatever we want, right?

44:50.933 --> 44:52.894
Whatever we want.

44:53.061 --> 44:54.645
Well, now.

44:54.812 --> 44:56.606
Who had the pie?

44:58.107 --> 44:59.650
Me.

45:03.488 --> 45:06.866
Whaddaya think? Are they me?

45:12.246 --> 45:14.248
- Don't look now.
- Why?

45:14.415 --> 45:16.417
The guy over in the corner.

45:17.251 --> 45:19.670
Don't look! He was staring at us.

45:19.837 --> 45:23.216
Don't you think that guy
looks exactly like Quilty?

45:23.383 --> 45:25.843
What, the dentist?

45:26.010 --> 45:28.596
Of course not. His brother.

45:28.763 --> 45:31.849
The writer Quilty.
You know, he writes the plays.

45:32.016 --> 45:35.269
The smoking guy.
He smokes the Dromes in the ad.

45:35.436 --> 45:37.605
We saw him in the lobby with his dog.

45:53.079 --> 45:55.623
If I tell you how naughty I was at camp,...

45:57.417 --> 45:59.419
..you promise you won't be mad?

46:00.420 --> 46:02.422
Tell me later.

46:06.217 --> 46:08.219
I want you to go to bed.

46:09.887 --> 46:12.015
I'll go downstairs while you...

46:13.349 --> 46:15.893
When I come up, I want you to be asleep.

46:16.769 --> 46:18.271
All right?

46:29.991 --> 46:32.076
I've been such a disgusting girl.

46:33.244 --> 46:35.246
Just let me tell you.

46:35.413 --> 46:37.415
Tell me tomorrow.

46:38.624 --> 46:40.626
I'm going to go now. All right?

46:42.253 --> 46:44.255
Good night, Dad.

46:56.100 --> 46:58.102
Night-night.

47:08.905 --> 47:10.907
<i>Gentlewomen of the jury,...</i>

47:12.658 --> 47:15.536
<i>..if my happiness could have talked,...</i>

47:15.703 --> 47:19.707
<i>..it would have filled that hotel
with a deafening roar.</i>

47:20.583 --> 47:22.585
<i>My only regret...</i>

47:22.752 --> 47:27.006
<i>..is that I did not immediately deposit
key number 342 at the office...</i>

47:27.173 --> 47:31.803
<i>..and leave the town, the country,
the planet, that very night.</i>

47:31.969 --> 47:38.059
The Lord knows all,
the Lord sees all, the Lord forgives all.

47:58.871 --> 48:01.290
Where the devil did you get her?

48:08.548 --> 48:12.218
- I beg your pardon?
- I said the weather's getting better.

48:18.474 --> 48:20.476
It seems so.

48:20.643 --> 48:22.645
Who's the lassie?

48:26.566 --> 48:28.568
Um...

48:30.445 --> 48:32.447
It's my daughter.

48:32.613 --> 48:35.408
You lie. She's not.

48:36.826 --> 48:37.785
What?

48:39.203 --> 48:41.205
I said July was hot.

48:43.708 --> 48:46.210
Where's her mother?

48:47.336 --> 48:49.338
Dead.

48:49.505 --> 48:51.466
Oh. Sorry.

48:51.632 --> 48:54.177
Why don't you two
lunch with me tomorrow?

48:54.343 --> 48:57.430
That clerical crowd will be gone soon.

48:58.097 --> 49:00.099
Um...

49:00.558 --> 49:02.560
We'll be gone too, thanks.

49:02.727 --> 49:04.228
Good night.

49:04.395 --> 49:07.440
Sorry. I'm very drunk. Good night.

49:11.277 --> 49:14.447
That child of yours needs a lot of sleep.

49:14.614 --> 49:17.325
"Sleep is a rose" the Persians say.

49:19.827 --> 49:21.829
Smoke?

49:21.996 --> 49:24.207
Not just now, thanks.

49:29.879 --> 49:32.340
Good night.

49:33.174 --> 49:35.176
Enjoy.

51:35.171 --> 51:38.883
Get back in the boat with Charlie.
You don't have to do that.

51:42.011 --> 51:44.222
Back in the boat.

52:02.156 --> 52:04.158
I'm thirsty.

52:09.664 --> 52:11.666
I'll bring you something.

54:47.739 --> 54:50.950
You... You played that with Charlie?
At camp?

54:51.117 --> 54:55.246
Don't tell me you never tried it
when you were a kid.

54:57.498 --> 54:59.709
Never.

55:02.003 --> 55:04.881
I guess I'm gonna have to
show you everything.

55:29.489 --> 55:31.491
<i>Gentlewomen of the jury,...</i>

55:31.657 --> 55:33.659
<i>..I was not even her first lover.</i>

55:46.964 --> 55:48.966
What are you reading?

55:49.133 --> 55:51.010
Nothing.

55:53.346 --> 55:55.473
What's the matter?

55:57.600 --> 55:59.185
Nothing.

56:01.187 --> 56:03.189
Lo...

56:05.441 --> 56:08.903
You know that friend of yours
- Charlie - at camp?

56:10.446 --> 56:12.448
Was he the first one?

56:12.615 --> 56:15.159
Can we please get off the subject?

56:23.710 --> 56:25.962
<i>I felt more and more uncomfortable.</i>

56:27.922 --> 56:30.883
<i>It was something quite special,
that feeling.</i>

56:31.259 --> 56:33.803
<i>An oppressive, hideous constraint,...</i>

56:33.970 --> 56:38.558
<i>..as if I were sitting with the small ghost
of somebody I had just killed.</i>

56:41.894 --> 56:43.271
Jesus!

56:43.438 --> 56:44.939
What?

56:45.106 --> 56:47.358
Can we stop at a gas station?

56:47.525 --> 56:49.944
We can go anywhere you like.

56:50.111 --> 56:52.113
Well, I need a gas station.

56:52.280 --> 56:54.073
I hurt inside.

56:57.160 --> 56:59.245
Well, what do you expect?

56:59.412 --> 57:03.041
I was a daisy-fresh girl,
and look what you've done to me.

57:03.207 --> 57:08.004
I should call the police and tell them
that you raped me, you dirty old man.

57:30.610 --> 57:33.905
- Just wash the windscreen, would you?
- Yes, sir.

58:07.689 --> 58:09.273
Got some cookies.

58:11.317 --> 58:14.529
I want to call Mother in hospital.
What's the number?

58:16.155 --> 58:18.366
Get in. You can't call the hospital.

58:18.533 --> 58:20.326
Why not?

58:21.536 --> 58:23.287
Just get in the car.

58:27.083 --> 58:28.584
Slam the door.

58:31.462 --> 58:34.173
Why can't I call my own mother
if I want to?

58:36.926 --> 58:38.928
Because your mother's dead.

59:35.735 --> 59:37.737
Shh... Shh...

59:48.581 --> 59:51.501
<i>We made up very gently that night.</i>

59:51.667 --> 59:54.712
<i>You see, she had nowhere else to go.</i>

01:00:01.761 --> 01:00:04.972
<i>It was then that we began
our extensive travels...</i>

01:00:05.139 --> 01:00:07.141
<i>..all over the United States.</i>

01:00:07.308 --> 01:00:11.813
<i># Now the native population
and civilisation is fine</i>

01:00:14.399 --> 01:00:18.903
<i># That civilisation
is the thing for me to see</i>

01:00:20.988 --> 01:00:23.825
<i># Whoa, bongo, bongo, bongo</i>

01:00:23.991 --> 01:00:26.994
<i># I don't wanna leave the Congo,
no, no, no, no, no, no</i>

01:00:29.789 --> 01:00:34.585
- When's the best time to buy a bird?
- I don't know. When's the best time?

01:00:34.752 --> 01:00:36.713
When it's going "cheep!"

01:00:36.879 --> 01:00:39.132
Don't say I never gave you anything.

01:00:40.967 --> 01:00:42.844
Ow! Don't! I'm trying to drive!

01:00:46.556 --> 01:00:48.307
Don't do that! Oh, no!

01:00:49.976 --> 01:00:52.061
If it goes out the window, I won't stop.

01:00:52.228 --> 01:00:55.148
Don't! What are these? Hair grips?

01:01:05.366 --> 01:01:07.076
<i># Civilisation</i>

01:01:07.243 --> 01:01:08.661
<i># No, no, no, no</i>

01:01:08.828 --> 01:01:10.830
<i># I'll stay right here</i>

01:01:19.297 --> 01:01:21.299
Look! They have Magic Fingers.

01:01:22.717 --> 01:01:24.469
Good.

01:01:24.635 --> 01:01:26.637
I need to shower.

01:01:28.056 --> 01:01:30.058
Give me a quarter and a dime.

01:01:30.224 --> 01:01:31.726
What for?

01:01:31.893 --> 01:01:34.145
For the Magic Fingers.

01:01:35.229 --> 01:01:37.440
My magic fingers aren't enough?

01:02:04.842 --> 01:02:11.516
# Amor-r-r, amor-r-r, amor-r-r-r-r

01:02:11.683 --> 01:02:16.688
# This w-word s-so s-sweet that I r-repeat

01:02:16.854 --> 01:02:20.608
# Means I adore you-u-u-u-u

01:02:20.775 --> 01:02:27.490
# Amor-r-r-r-r, amor-r-r-r-r, amor-r-r-r-r...

01:02:30.034 --> 01:02:32.036
Good shower for once, Lo!

01:02:32.203 --> 01:02:34.580
First-rate temperature control!

01:02:53.725 --> 01:02:55.268
Ow! Argh!

01:02:55.435 --> 01:02:58.563
- Agh! Lo!
- Hmm?

01:02:58.730 --> 01:03:01.941
My God, Lo!
Don't flush when I'm in here!

01:03:26.716 --> 01:03:28.718
What is that?

01:03:29.886 --> 01:03:31.888
What's what?

01:03:36.100 --> 01:03:38.519
That thing in your mouth.

01:03:38.686 --> 01:03:40.688
It's a jawbreaker.

01:03:41.814 --> 01:03:45.276
It's supposed to break your jaw.
Want one?

01:03:45.443 --> 01:03:48.905
Just give it to me.
I've had it with that noise.

01:03:53.368 --> 01:03:56.788
- Come on, spit it out. I've got a headache.
- It's good!

01:03:56.954 --> 01:04:00.541
Look, just give it to me, will you?
Spit it out.

01:04:31.406 --> 01:04:34.826
You look a hundred per cent better
when I can't see you.

01:04:34.992 --> 01:04:37.787
<i>We took a circuitous route -
to put it mildly.</i>

01:04:37.954 --> 01:04:41.249
<i>In the back of my mind
was our eventual destination.</i>

01:04:41.416 --> 01:04:46.963
<i>Beardsley College, where I would finally
take up my teaching position.</i>

01:04:47.130 --> 01:04:52.093
<i>But in the front of my mind was
the need to keep going, keep driving.</i>

01:04:53.928 --> 01:04:57.390
Lo, that's the last time
I let you drive this car.

01:04:57.557 --> 01:04:58.808
Serve into this square.

01:05:00.643 --> 01:05:02.145
<i>And, despite our tiffs,...</i>

01:05:03.521 --> 01:05:06.691
In the square, Lo.
Try and get it in the square.

01:05:06.858 --> 01:05:11.320
<i>..despite the fuss she made, and
the danger and hopelessness of it all,...</i>

01:05:11.487 --> 01:05:12.947
Aim for my head.

01:05:13.114 --> 01:05:16.034
<i>..despite all that, I was in paradise.</i>

01:05:18.995 --> 01:05:22.999
<i>A paradise whose skies
were the colour of hell flames,...</i>

01:05:25.293 --> 01:05:27.295
<i>..but a paradise still.</i>

01:09:18.734 --> 01:09:22.321
I know you have accepted a post
at Beardsley College,...

01:09:22.488 --> 01:09:26.993
..and I know that there,
academics are first, last and always.

01:09:27.160 --> 01:09:30.580
Well, that's not us, Mr Himmler.

01:09:30.747 --> 01:09:33.499
Uh... Here at Beardsley Prep,...

01:09:33.666 --> 01:09:35.752
..what we stress are the three Ds.

01:09:35.917 --> 01:09:39.212
Dramatics, dancing and dating.

01:09:39.380 --> 01:09:44.260
Now, I know that the Reverend Rigger is
behind us on this. Aren't you, Reverend?

01:09:44.426 --> 01:09:48.180
- All the way, Miss Pratt. Every inch.
- So you see, Mr Humper,...

01:09:48.348 --> 01:09:53.435
..for the modern preadolescent, medieval
dates are less vital than weekend ones.

01:09:55.271 --> 01:09:58.358
- What? Weekend what?
- Dates, Mr Humping.

01:09:58.524 --> 01:10:01.194
Uh... boys.

01:10:10.912 --> 01:10:12.914
<i># By myself alone at home</i>

01:10:13.081 --> 01:10:14.665
<i># Feelin' blue</i>

01:10:14.832 --> 01:10:18.795
<i>I was not quite prepared
for the reality of my dual role.</i>

01:10:18.961 --> 01:10:22.548
<i>On the one hand,
the willing corrupter of an innocent,...</i>

01:10:22.715 --> 01:10:25.677
<i>..and on the other,
Humbert the happy housewife.</i>

01:10:27.887 --> 01:10:29.889
Where's the river Rhine?

01:10:31.766 --> 01:10:33.768
I don't know.

01:10:33.935 --> 01:10:35.937
You should know that.

01:10:36.104 --> 01:10:39.065
- Why?
- Big battles there in the Great War.

01:10:42.235 --> 01:10:44.237
Where's the river Seine?

01:10:45.905 --> 01:10:47.907
I don't know.

01:10:48.074 --> 01:10:51.536
I thought you were supposed
to have learnt these.

01:10:51.703 --> 01:10:53.705
