Lo...

01:36:38.583 --> 01:36:40.585
Lo, I'm sorry.

01:36:40.752 --> 01:36:43.421
- I'm sorry!

01:36:51.137 --> 01:36:53.806
Come here. Come here.

01:36:53.931 --> 01:36:55.933
Get away!

01:36:57.435 --> 01:36:59.645
Lo...

01:36:59.812 --> 01:37:01.814
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

01:37:01.981 --> 01:37:03.441
I'm sorry.

01:37:28.383 --> 01:37:31.469
Shall I walk down to the town
and get you some fruit?

01:37:32.595 --> 01:37:34.597
Bananas.

01:37:43.481 --> 01:37:45.483
Just bananas?

01:37:46.818 --> 01:37:49.737
Just bananas.

01:38:01.290 --> 01:38:04.419
<i># Open the door, Richard</i>

01:38:04.585 --> 01:38:08.089
<i># Open the door and let me in</i>

01:38:08.256 --> 01:38:10.925
<i># Open the door, Richard</i>

01:38:11.050 --> 01:38:15.763
<i>- # Richard...</i>
- # Why don't you open that door?

01:38:24.897 --> 01:38:29.027
<i># Borrow confidently from HFC</i>

01:38:29.193 --> 01:38:33.823
<i>Quilty can't be here in our studio
because he's in Wace, Texas tonight...</i>

01:38:33.990 --> 01:38:36.993
<i>..working on the premiere
of his brand-new play.</i>

01:38:37.160 --> 01:38:39.996
<i>But I want to welcome
his writing partner,...</i>

01:38:40.163 --> 01:38:43.291
<i>..the lovely and talented
Miss Vivian Darkbloom.</i>

01:38:43.458 --> 01:38:45.668
<i>Let's give her a warm Texas welcome.</i>

01:39:16.115 --> 01:39:18.284
You've been out.

01:39:19.410 --> 01:39:21.412
I just got up.

01:39:26.542 --> 01:39:28.544
Don't lie to me.

01:39:32.715 --> 01:39:34.717
Well, I did go out for a second.

01:39:35.927 --> 01:39:39.722
You were gone so long.
I wanted to see if you were coming back.

01:40:29.564 --> 01:40:32.525
You tell me who it is! Who is it?

01:40:32.692 --> 01:40:35.194
Who is it? Tell me who it is.

01:40:37.196 --> 01:40:39.615
You tell me. Who is it?

01:40:40.616 --> 01:40:41.534
Who...?

01:40:41.701 --> 01:40:44.495
- Tell me.

01:40:44.662 --> 01:40:45.747
Please, tell me.

01:40:57.967 --> 01:40:59.594
Please tell me.

01:40:59.761 --> 01:41:01.763
Please tell me.

01:41:13.524 --> 01:41:15.318
Please tell me.

01:41:17.487 --> 01:41:19.030
Please!

01:41:19.197 --> 01:41:21.032
Please... tell... me!

01:41:21.199 --> 01:41:23.201
Please... please...

01:41:24.243 --> 01:41:26.245
Please...

01:41:26.412 --> 01:41:28.414
..tell me!

01:41:28.581 --> 01:41:29.791
Please...

01:41:29.957 --> 01:41:31.167
..please...

01:41:31.334 --> 01:41:32.669
..please...

01:43:19.776 --> 01:43:21.778
I'll show you to room number 29.

01:43:21.944 --> 01:43:23.946
It's one of our nicer rooms.

01:43:24.113 --> 01:43:27.492
Say, what's wrong
with your little daughter? Is she ill?

01:43:27.659 --> 01:43:30.078
Oh, no. She's just feeling a bit... um...

01:43:34.040 --> 01:43:35.625
My God, Lo!

01:43:35.792 --> 01:43:37.377
Are you all right?

01:43:38.378 --> 01:43:41.047
I don't feel... I don't feel very well.

01:43:41.881 --> 01:43:43.883
It's a virus.

01:43:44.050 --> 01:43:47.136
Nothing serious.
I've had 40 cases in two weeks.

01:43:47.303 --> 01:43:50.973
- So can I take her home?
- We're gonna keep her here overnight.

01:43:51.140 --> 01:43:53.309
Keep her hydrated, help her sleep.

01:44:04.529 --> 01:44:08.074
Why don't you get some sleep?
It won't help if you catch it.

01:44:08.241 --> 01:44:10.702
I think I have already.
I feel dreadful.

01:44:10.868 --> 01:44:12.870
- Maybe I should stay.
- Go.

01:44:13.037 --> 01:44:14.956
Call us in the morning.

01:44:15.123 --> 01:44:17.333
- Here, I'll take those.
- Thank you.

01:44:47.321 --> 01:44:49.449
Uh, yes, hello. This is Mr Humbert.

01:44:49.615 --> 01:44:53.536
I'm calling to see how my... daughter,
Dolores Haze, is.

01:44:53.703 --> 01:44:55.705
Oh, she's much better.

01:44:55.872 --> 01:44:58.166
She was up early. No trace of fever.

01:44:58.333 --> 01:45:01.586
And when Uncle Gustave came for her,
we signed her out.

01:45:03.338 --> 01:45:06.007
Who? Wh... Wh... Who?

01:45:06.132 --> 01:45:08.384
Uncle Gustave, Dolores called him.

01:45:08.551 --> 01:45:12.180
He had a sweet little dog.
He was the nicest man. Had a big smile.

01:45:12.347 --> 01:45:13.723
Wait, Ted.

01:45:13.890 --> 01:45:17.935
- And you let her go with him?
- Oh, yes. He paid the bill in cash.

01:45:18.102 --> 01:45:22.940
They said to tell you not to worry,
and they'll be at Grandpa's expecting you.

01:45:23.107 --> 01:45:26.778
- Then they went off in that nice Cadillac.

01:45:26.944 --> 01:45:28.946
Hello?

01:45:47.048 --> 01:45:48.591
Hey!

01:45:48.758 --> 01:45:50.426
Hey!

01:46:00.311 --> 01:46:01.270
Nurse!

01:46:01.437 --> 01:46:03.439
- Where is she?
- Who?

01:46:03.606 --> 01:46:06.067
Who took her?
Somebody took my daughter.

01:46:06.234 --> 01:46:09.195
- You need to talk to the doctor.
- But who took her?

01:46:09.362 --> 01:46:11.531
My daughter was in there last night.

01:46:11.698 --> 01:46:13.992
- Who took her away?
- Hey, relax, pal!

01:46:14.158 --> 01:46:17.620
Don't tell me to relax!
I'm looking for my daughter! Doctor!

01:46:17.787 --> 01:46:19.497
Doctor! Doctor!

01:46:19.664 --> 01:46:21.666
What have you done with her?

01:46:21.833 --> 01:46:23.918
Where is she? Where is she?

01:46:24.127 --> 01:46:26.838
Tell me where she is! Where is she?

01:46:27.005 --> 01:46:29.590
Where has she gone?
Where? Where? Where?

01:46:32.051 --> 01:46:34.137
You leave me alone, you bastards!

01:46:34.303 --> 01:46:36.014
You fucking fiends!

01:46:36.180 --> 01:46:38.182
Tell me where she is!

01:46:40.435 --> 01:46:42.437
Get me to that man!

01:46:44.313 --> 01:46:46.858
I'm just looking for my daughter!

01:46:48.026 --> 01:46:51.571
- I said relax!
- I want to know where she -

01:46:53.531 --> 01:46:56.242
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Sorry, sorry, sorry.

01:46:56.409 --> 01:46:57.869
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:46:58.036 --> 01:46:59.746
Sorry.

01:46:59.912 --> 01:47:02.081
I'm sorry. I'm just a little bit...

01:47:02.248 --> 01:47:06.127
I think I may just have...
had a little too much to drink. Sorry.

01:47:06.294 --> 01:47:09.589
I'm very worried
about my daughter, you see.

01:47:09.756 --> 01:47:12.216
But she's with her Uncle Gustave.

01:47:12.383 --> 01:47:14.385
So she'll be all right.

01:47:14.552 --> 01:47:16.721
I'm very sorry. Please forgive me.

01:47:16.888 --> 01:47:19.223
She's gone to her... grandpa's farm.

01:47:20.350 --> 01:47:22.435
She'll be absolutely fine there.

01:47:22.602 --> 01:47:24.604
What better place for her?

01:47:24.771 --> 01:47:27.106
I'm... I'm fine.

01:47:27.273 --> 01:47:29.275
Please, I'm sorry.

01:47:29.442 --> 01:47:31.444
So sorry. Thank you very much.

01:47:31.611 --> 01:47:33.613
Sorry... Sorry.

01:47:33.780 --> 01:47:35.782
So sorry.

01:47:50.838 --> 01:47:52.840
<i>I searched all our old haunts...</i>

01:47:53.007 --> 01:47:56.594
<i>..and for several months
the trail remained warm.</i>

01:47:59.180 --> 01:48:03.559
<i>The thief, the kidnapper,
whatever you want to call him,...</i>

01:48:03.726 --> 01:48:05.395
<i>..he was clever.</i>

01:48:05.561 --> 01:48:07.563
<i>He would disguise his name.</i>

01:48:07.730 --> 01:48:10.274
<i>But I could always tell his handwriting.</i>

01:48:11.776 --> 01:48:13.569
Um... Sir!

01:48:17.824 --> 01:48:19.909
<i>He had very peculiar Ts, Ws and Ls.</i>

01:48:20.076 --> 01:48:22.578
Do you know his name?

01:48:24.163 --> 01:48:26.165
What does he look like?

01:48:28.626 --> 01:48:30.628
- Let me help.
- No, please...

01:48:32.630 --> 01:48:35.216
Ladies, I'm sorry. We're trying to find...

01:48:35.383 --> 01:48:38.636
<i>It must be hard
for you who already know who it was...</i>

01:48:38.803 --> 01:48:41.055
<i>..to understand my mystification.</i>

01:48:49.647 --> 01:48:52.316
<i>Or maybe you think
I was imagining things.</i>

01:48:52.483 --> 01:48:54.068
..my daughter.

01:48:55.361 --> 01:49:00.074
<i>Maybe you think it impossible that
there could have been another like me.</i>

01:49:00.241 --> 01:49:05.038
<i>Another mad lover of nymphets following
us over the great and ugly plains.</i>

01:49:05.204 --> 01:49:07.415
<i>Well, you are right, of course.</i>

01:49:07.582 --> 01:49:09.584
<i>There was no-one else like me.</i>

01:49:18.843 --> 01:49:21.387
<i>Eventually the trail went cold and dead.</i>

01:49:25.683 --> 01:49:28.353
<i>And I went back to cold, dead Beardsley.</i>

01:50:23.032 --> 01:50:25.910
"Dear Dad, how's everything?"

01:50:26.911 --> 01:50:29.330
"I'm married. I'm going to have a baby."

01:50:31.666 --> 01:50:34.377
"I guess it'll come
right around Christmas."

01:50:36.337 --> 01:50:38.464
"This is a hard letter to write."

01:50:38.631 --> 01:50:41.592
"I'm going nuts
because we don't have enough...

01:50:41.759 --> 01:50:44.095
..to pay our debts and get out of here."

01:50:45.638 --> 01:50:48.391
"Dick has been promised
a big job in Alaska."

01:50:50.977 --> 01:50:52.979
"Are you still mad at me?"

01:50:54.188 --> 01:50:59.110
"Please send us a cheque, Dad. We could
manage with three or four hundred,...

01:50:59.277 --> 01:51:01.654
..or even less. Anything is welcome."

01:51:02.447 --> 01:51:05.616
"I have gone through
much sadness and hardship."

01:51:05.783 --> 01:51:07.785
"Yours expecting, Dolly."

01:51:09.454 --> 01:51:11.456
"Mrs Richard F...

01:51:13.583 --> 01:51:15.585
..Schiller."

01:52:34.998 --> 01:52:37.375
Well!

01:53:08.239 --> 01:53:10.241
Come in.

01:53:23.212 --> 01:53:25.214
You, Molly, stay out.

01:53:25.381 --> 01:53:27.216
Good girl.

01:53:27.383 --> 01:53:29.802
Husband at home?

01:53:29.969 --> 01:53:31.763
Yeah.

01:53:31.929 --> 01:53:34.891
Where do you wanna sit?
The rocker or the divan?

01:53:35.975 --> 01:53:37.977
Come sit with me on the divan.

01:53:44.859 --> 01:53:46.444
Is that him?

01:53:47.904 --> 01:53:49.864
Up the ladder?

01:53:50.031 --> 01:53:52.700
You want me to call him in?

01:53:53.618 --> 01:53:55.370
No.

01:53:55.536 --> 01:53:58.206
He's not the one I want.

01:53:59.957 --> 01:54:02.251
He's not the what?

01:54:02.418 --> 01:54:04.545
You know what I mean.

01:54:04.712 --> 01:54:06.923
Where is he?

01:54:07.090 --> 01:54:09.092
Look...

01:54:09.676 --> 01:54:14.222
Dick has nothing to do with all that stuff.
He thinks you're my father.

01:54:14.389 --> 01:54:16.641
Please don't bring up all that muck.

01:54:18.393 --> 01:54:21.729
- All right, I'll find out myself.
- You really don't know?

01:54:28.987 --> 01:54:30.989
My God, Dad, it was Quilty.

01:54:31.155 --> 01:54:33.282
It was Clare Quilty.

01:54:41.416 --> 01:54:43.418
Yes.

01:54:48.923 --> 01:54:51.050
Yes, of course.

01:55:10.111 --> 01:55:11.904
Quilty.

01:55:13.031 --> 01:55:15.033
Yeah.

01:55:17.243 --> 01:55:20.913
He was the only man
I was ever really crazy about.

01:55:25.710 --> 01:55:27.920
What about me?

01:55:55.490 --> 01:55:57.492
Where did he take you?

01:56:01.537 --> 01:56:03.790
Just tell me.

01:56:04.999 --> 01:56:07.835
Well, everybody knew he liked little girls.

01:56:08.002 --> 01:56:12.882
He used to film them in his mansion
over in Parkington, Pavor Manor.

01:56:15.343 --> 01:56:18.513
But I wasn't gonna do all those things.

01:56:20.014 --> 01:56:22.016
All what things?

01:56:22.183 --> 01:56:24.268
Two girls and two boys or...

01:56:24.435 --> 01:56:26.521
..I don't know, three or four men.

01:56:26.688 --> 01:56:29.148
And Vivian was filming the whole thing.

01:56:29.315 --> 01:56:33.152
I said "No, I'm not gonna blow
all those beastly boys."

01:56:33.319 --> 01:56:35.446
"I want you."

01:56:38.783 --> 01:56:40.660
So he threw me out.

01:56:50.420 --> 01:56:52.422
<i>I looked and looked at her...</i>

01:56:54.465 --> 01:56:57.760
<i>..and I knew,
as clearly as I know that I will die,...</i>

01:56:57.927 --> 01:57:02.515
<i>..that I loved her more than anything
I'd ever seen or imagined on earth.</i>

01:57:06.644 --> 01:57:10.606
<i>She was only the dead leaf echo
of the nymphet from long ago...</i>

01:57:11.858 --> 01:57:14.235
<i>..but I loved her, this Lolita,...</i>

01:57:14.402 --> 01:57:17.864
<i>..pale and polluted
and big with another man's child.</i>

01:57:18.031 --> 01:57:21.200
<i>She could fade and wither - I didn't care.</i>

01:57:23.202 --> 01:57:25.872
<i>I would still go mad with tenderness...</i>

01:57:25.997 --> 01:57:27.999
<i>..at the mere sight of her face.</i>

01:57:51.522 --> 01:57:53.524
Lolita...

01:57:55.818 --> 01:57:59.906
From here to that old car
that you know so well...

01:58:00.073 --> 01:58:02.325
..is a stretch of 25 paces.

01:58:05.119 --> 01:58:07.622
Make those 25 steps...

01:58:07.789 --> 01:58:09.791
..with me, now.

01:58:09.957 --> 01:58:14.379
You're saying you'll give us some money
if I go to a motel with you?

01:58:14.545 --> 01:58:16.506
No... No!

01:58:16.673 --> 01:58:21.177
I'm saying leave here and come live
with me, die with me, everything with me.

01:58:22.345 --> 01:58:24.347
You're crazy.

01:58:24.514 --> 01:58:27.225
If you refuse, you still get the money.

01:58:27.392 --> 01:58:28.810
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:58:30.603 --> 01:58:32.605
There. Have it.

01:58:41.614 --> 01:58:43.491
Oh my God.

01:58:43.658 --> 01:58:46.953
You're giving us four thousand bucks?

01:58:50.206 --> 01:58:51.833
- Thank you...
- No...

01:58:52.000 --> 01:58:54.002
Don't touch me.

01:58:54.168 --> 01:58:56.170
I'll die if you touch me.

01:58:57.505 --> 01:59:02.218
Just tell me...
there's a chance you'll come with me.

01:59:04.012 --> 01:59:06.014
No, honey.

01:59:06.180 --> 01:59:08.516
I'd almost rather go back with Clare.

01:59:11.978 --> 01:59:13.980
Oh...

01:59:14.147 --> 01:59:16.149
I'll go now.

01:59:18.276 --> 01:59:22.613
- Can I call Dick in to say goodbye?
- No. I don't want to see him, at all.

01:59:22.780 --> 01:59:25.825
I just want to go.

01:59:35.293 --> 01:59:38.504
Lo, can you ever forget
what I've done to you?

01:59:43.676 --> 01:59:45.678
Say goodbye, Molly.

01:59:46.763 --> 01:59:48.765
Say goodbye to my dad.

02:00:56.040 --> 02:00:58.126
Dick! Guess what!

02:01:19.063 --> 02:01:21.399
<i>Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,...</i>

02:01:21.566 --> 02:01:26.487
<i>..I have to say that I regret all I did
before that last goodbye in Coalmont.</i>

02:01:28.531 --> 02:01:32.118
<i>But I regret nothing of what came after.</i>

02:03:08.089 --> 02:03:10.091
Now, who are you?

02:03:13.886 --> 02:03:15.972
Are you, by any chance, Brewster?

02:03:22.353 --> 02:03:25.148
You know, you don't look
like Jack Brewster.

02:03:25.314 --> 02:03:28.818
I mean, the resemblance
is not particularly striking.

02:03:28.985 --> 02:03:33.489
Somebody told me he had a brother
with the same phone company.

02:03:33.656 --> 02:03:35.658
I'm neither of the Brewsters.

02:03:42.707 --> 02:03:44.208
Pull over!

02:03:45.293 --> 02:03:46.794
Pull over!

02:03:50.006 --> 02:03:52.425
Do you recall a little girl named...

02:03:54.260 --> 02:03:56.054
..Dolores Haze?

02:04:00.266 --> 02:04:02.685
You see, I'm her father.

02:04:04.062 --> 02:04:05.563
Nonsense.

02:04:05.730 --> 02:04:09.192
You're a foreigner.
You're an agent of a foreign power.

02:04:09.359 --> 02:04:11.444
You're a foreign literary agent.

02:04:11.611 --> 02:04:14.030
She was my daughter.

02:04:14.197 --> 02:04:16.199
She was my child.

02:04:16.366 --> 02:04:18.743
Oh, you know,
I adore children myself.

02:04:18.910 --> 02:04:20.912
And fathers...

02:04:21.079 --> 02:04:23.122
I love fathers.

02:04:26.668 --> 02:04:28.461
Ah...

02:04:28.628 --> 02:04:29.587
Sit down!

02:04:31.297 --> 02:04:33.299
Oh. There they are.

02:04:33.466 --> 02:04:35.718
Now we need matches.
You got a light?

02:04:35.885 --> 02:04:38.471
Quilty, I want you to concentrate.

02:04:41.849 --> 02:04:43.518
You're about to die.

02:04:43.685 --> 02:04:46.020
Ooh.

02:04:53.987 --> 02:04:55.571
Jesus!

02:04:56.948 --> 02:05:01.244
Do you want to be executed
standing up or sitting down?

02:05:01.411 --> 02:05:04.831
Just let me think, let me think.
It's not an easy question.

02:05:04.998 --> 02:05:07.458
Try to understand what is happening.

02:05:07.625 --> 02:05:08.459
I- I- I- I...

02:05:08.626 --> 02:05:12.005
- Remember Dolores Haze.
- I'm willing...

02:05:12.171 --> 02:05:15.508
I'm willing to try. I am. Just...

02:05:15.675 --> 02:05:17.343
OK. Listen.

02:05:17.510 --> 02:05:19.512
I made a mistake, which I regret,...

02:05:19.679 --> 02:05:21.597
..sincerely.

02:05:21.764 --> 02:05:27.270
I couldn't have any fun with your Dolly.
I'm practically impotent is the sad truth.

02:05:27.437 --> 02:05:32.150
But she had a swell vacation, met some
remarkable people. Hey, do you know -

02:05:46.873 --> 02:05:48.333
Stay still!

02:05:50.043 --> 02:05:52.003
Oh, God...

02:05:52.837 --> 02:05:54.839
You cheated me.

02:05:57.467 --> 02:05:59.469
You cheated me of my redemption.

02:06:01.971 --> 02:06:05.641
- You have to die.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

02:06:05.808 --> 02:06:09.645
My memory and my eloquence
are not at their best today.

02:06:09.812 --> 02:06:14.150
But really, you have to admit
you were never an ideal stepfather.

02:06:14.317 --> 02:06:16.319
Hm?

02:06:16.486 --> 02:06:18.946
I did not force your protégée to join me.

02:06:19.113 --> 02:06:22.116
It was she who made me
remove her to a happier home.

02:06:22.283 --> 02:06:24.577
Look around you. See?

02:06:24.744 --> 02:06:26.746
You see this house?

02:06:26.913 --> 02:06:31.501
It's very cool in the summer. Comfortable.
I suggest that you move in, hm?

02:06:34.337 --> 02:06:36.547
I think you'll be happy here.

02:06:37.632 --> 02:06:39.634
You can use my wardrobe.

02:06:40.593 --> 02:06:43.763
We have the most reliable
and bribable charwoman.

02:06:43.930 --> 02:06:46.391
"Cleaning lady" is the American term.

02:06:46.557 --> 02:06:50.144
She has not only daughters,
she has granddaughters.

02:06:50.311 --> 02:06:53.606
And I know a thing or two
about the chief of police...

02:06:53.773 --> 02:06:55.817
..that makes him my slave.

02:06:55.984 --> 02:06:58.069
My slave. Drop the gun.

02:06:58.236 --> 02:07:00.738
And here's another thing...--
Drop the gun.

02:07:00.905 --> 02:07:04.784
...I have, upstairs,
the most unique collection of erotica.

02:07:04.951 --> 02:07:06.327
Drop the gun. Drop the gun.

02:07:06.494 --> 02:07:10.623
Also, moreover, I can arrange
for you to attend executions.

02:07:10.790 --> 02:07:13.793
Not everybody knows
the chair is painted yellow.

02:07:16.295 --> 02:07:17.672
Somebody help!

02:08:23.321 --> 02:08:24.989
Aargh! Agh!

02:08:25.990 --> 02:08:27.992
That hurts, sir.

02:08:28.159 --> 02:08:30.745
That hurts atrociously, my dear fellow.

02:08:41.422 --> 02:08:43.424
God...

02:08:43.591 --> 02:08:46.678
You should not continue
in this fashion, really.

02:09:17.375 --> 02:09:19.168
Get out!

02:09:19.335 --> 02:09:21.004
Get out of here!

02:11:30.383 --> 02:11:33.761
<i>What I heard then was
the melody of children at play.</i>

02:11:33.928 --> 02:11:35.930
<i>Nothing but that.</i>

02:11:38.307 --> 02:11:41.477
<i>And I knew that
the hopelessly poignant thing...</i>

02:11:41.644 --> 02:11:44.480
<i>..was not Lolita's absence from my side...</i>

02:11:46.149 --> 02:11:49.193
<i>..but the absence of her voice
from that chorus.</i>

